  "text": "Infection of cells and animals. Cell cultures were infected as described previously [CITATION_1] and incubated at 33 C for 72 hr in the presence of Eagle's basal medium (BME) supplemented with bovine serum albumin [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Hemagglutination. For hemagglutination, adult goose erythrocytes (GE) were used [CITATION_4] . Blood was preserved in equal parts of Alsever's solution and was stored at 4 C. For each experiment, the cells were washed four times with PBS and taken up as a 0.25% suspension in phosphate buffer (pH 6.4).",
